<anchor id="hit__detect_8h_1hit_detect"/> <simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>Based on the requirements medium * and critical hits for vertical (z) direction shall be calculated automatically from the measured raw accelerator data. <linebreak/>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Impacts (only vertical)<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>300 m/s² for 8ms shall be counted as medium hit</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>800 m/s² for 2ms shall be counted as critical hit The medium hit counter shall be incremented if the acceleration exceeds the threshold on z-axis of 300 m/s² and return to normal within 8 ms, which corresponds to 32 or less samples by a sample frequency of 4400 Hz. If the acceleration persists and continue for more than 8 ms (more than 32 samples), it shall be not longer treated as a medium hit because it’s sustained and not just a momentary spike. <linebreak/>
 The critical hit counter shall be incremented if the acceleration exceeds the threshold on z-axis of 800 m/s² and return to normal within 2 ms, which corresponds to 8 or less samples by a sample frequency of 4400 Hz. if the acceleration persists and continue for more than 2 ms (more than 8 samples), it is no longer treated as a critical hit because it’s sustained and not just a momentary spike.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
